Description:
I came up with this awhile ago when I was playing with cooperative LLM agents. It is the simplest implementation of a message bus that I could think of. The architecture is very simple. Let's start with the following barebones python.
def main(): print("Hello, world.") if __name__=="__main__": main() Let's begin by looking at how we interact with our bus. In the main() function, add the following:
bus = MessageBus() def callback(message: str): print(f"Received message '{message}'") Now we need to sort out the bus.
